Arrange fish fillets in a 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray. Brush the top of each fillet with mayonnaise. Sprinkle with peanuts and pepper. Bake, uncovered, at 450 degrees F for 10-15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. meanwhile, combine the salsa ingredients in a bowl. Serve with the fish.